page.title: 18COASTLINE AND CAVES
page.content: The coastline around Catterline is all rocks;there is no sand just stones.The bay has suffered a lot from erosion . The road to the bay is often closed because of landslides. One big rock called Dunnie Woof is called the Dumpling by local people.It stands in the middle of the bay.People can climb to the top where there is grass.At one time the Dumpling would have been part of the cliff but it has been worn away by erosion.There are two smugglers' caves in the bay to the north which is called Trelong. The only way you can get into the cave is by boat.
